OL,3,CWhat happens now that Andy Burnham has
OL,4,Cwon the Makerfield by-election?
OL,6,FOnce a candidate has their numbers,
OL,7,Fthe National Executive Council (NEC) `
OL,8,FLabour Party's ruling body ` makes
OL,9,Farrangements for a full vote with
OL,10,Fparty members.
OL,12,FThere is also no formal limit on the
OL,13,Fnumber of candidates who can put
OL,14,Fthemselves forward to run, but they
OL,15,Fmust have the requisite backing.
OL,17,FAnd, MPs can only throw their support
OL,18,Fbehind one candidate at a time - in
OL,19,Fpractice, capping the opposition
OL,20,FStarmer could face if the contest is
OL,21,Ftriggered.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
